text:
East 149th Street, north side, east from but not including Bergen Ave. Also shown is the elevated structure of the Third Avenue elevated line extension to the Lexington Avenue subway line running on Westchester Ave.

May 1926.

Brown Brothers.

East 149th Street, west from Bergen Ave. as seen across the elevated trestle of the Third Ave. Elevated line. In the right background is visible the Immaculate Conception (Roman Catholic) Church, at the N.W. corner of Melrose Ave. and East 150th Street.

May 1926.

Brown Brothers.
